               <p>Tried by the first London Jury before Lord KENYON.</p>
               <p>Court to Jury. Gentlemen; it is not for me to dictate to you; but perhaps, if you were to re-consider the case of Elisha, you<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179104130032"></xptr>will find it stands totally on the evidence of the accomplice, which is not sufficient for conviction.</p>
               <p>The Jury deliberated some time, and then gave a verdict,</p>
               <p>ELISHA COLLIER, <rs id="t17910413-29-verdict162" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17910413-29-verdict162" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17910413-29-person365">
                  JANE
                   SHARPE
               <interp inst="t17910413-29-person365" type="surname" value="SHARPE"></interp>
